content:
All track participants, thank you attending and joining in the conversations around FHIR Testing and the TestScript resource.

I have published a draft of our Track Report Out. Please take a moment to review and let me know if there are any additions and/or corrections.

cc: @ryan moehrke

Looks good to me @Richard Ettema. Happy to take on the action item regarding TestScript/$execute and will circle back when I have something to show. I did also take another note that I will take a pass through our US Core Tests and identify the most complex parts to test, which might be useful to evaluate any proposed updates to TestScript against. I'll start threads on that over the next week or so.
And thanks for organizing and running the track!

@Robert Scanlon, thanks for the feedback. I've added another action item to the end of Session 1 for your note:

I did also take another note that I will take a pass through our US Core Tests and identify the most complex parts to test, which might be useful to evaluate any proposed updates to TestScript against.
